//roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/yildiz-teknik-1024x565.png","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/yildiz-teknik-1024x565.png","width":"200","height":"200","inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/yildiz-technical-university/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/yildiz-technical-university/","name":"Yıldız Technical University - RoadtoStudy","datePublished":"2025-10-07T15:41:22+03:00","dateModified":"2025-10-07T15:42:09+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"primaryImageOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/yildiz-teknik-1024x565.png"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/busra/","name":"busra","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/busra/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/a3c0f700b03ed22f8ab3a40880c2b539035a9a6e21bb16550f65e22a0ff39809?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/a3c0f700b03ed22f8ab3a40880c2b539035a9a6e21bb16550f65e22a0ff39809?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"busra","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"Article","headline":"Yıldız Technical University - RoadtoStudy","keywords":"Yıldız Technical University","datePublished":"2025-10-07T15:41:22+03:00","dateModified":"2025-10-07T15:42:09+03:00","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/busra/","name":"busra"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Yıldız Technical University (YTÜ) was founded in 1911 in Istanbul as the “Kondüktör Mekteb-i Alisi.” With a long-standing tradition in technical education,","name":"Yıldız Technical University - RoadtoStudy","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/yildiz-technical-university/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/yildiz-technical-university/#webpage"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/yildiz-teknik-1024x565.png"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/yildiz-technical-university/#webpage"}}]}]}'), '$.content_html', '<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="565" src="https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/yildiz-teknik-1024x565.png" alt="Yıldız Teknik Üniversitesi" class="wp-image-474" srcset="https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/yildiz-teknik-1024x565.png 1024w, https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/yildiz-teknik-300x166.png 300w, https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/yildiz-teknik-768x424.png 768w, https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/yildiz-teknik.png 1200w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">History and Vision of the University</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Yıldız Technical University (YTÜ) was founded in 1911 in Istanbul as the “Kondüktör Mekteb-i Alisi.” With a long-standing tradition in technical education, Yıldız Technical University took its current name and structure in 1982 under Law No. 2809. With a legacy spanning from the Ottoman Empire to the Republic, it is a leading institution in engineering and architecture. Led by Rector Prof. Dr. Tamer Yılmaz, YTÜ operates under the motto “Shaping the Future with Science and Technology.” Its vision is to become a globally leading research university. Its mission is to educate innovative, critically thinking individuals who contribute to society. With approximately 36,000 students (YÖK Atlas, 2022-2023), Yıldız Technical University ranks in the 801-1000 band in Times Higher Education 2025. YTÜ combines over a century of experience with modern science.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Education</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Yıldız Technical University offers academic diversity through 10 faculties: Architecture, Mechanical, Electrical-Electronics, Civil, Chemistry-Metallurgy, Arts and Sciences, Economics and Administrative Sciences, Naval Architecture and Maritime, Arts and Design, and Education. There are more than 80 undergraduate and over 150 graduate programs. Civil Engineering, Mechanical Engineering, and Architecture are particularly prominent. The academic staff of approximately 2,000 faculty members possesses international experience. The education model combines theoretical and practical learning, and some programs are offered in English. More than 200 laboratories and 20 research centers (e.g., YTÜ Teknopark) support practical skills. YTÜ is active in TÜBİTAK projects and is known for its scientific productivity.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">For more information, you can visit the <a href="http://www.yildiz.edu.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Yıldız Technical University</a> website.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Campus and Technological Infrastructure</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Yıldız Technical University’s main campuses are Yıldız and Davutpaşa. Yıldız Campus is located in Beşiktaş on a 120,000 m² historic site, while Davutpaşa Campus in Esenler spans 1.2 million m² of modern facilities. The campuses feature over 80 buildings totaling 350,000 m² of indoor space, with both historical and contemporary architectural designs. High-speed internet and smart classrooms form the core of technological infrastructure. Libraries provide access to over 500,000 printed resources and more than 1 million digital publications, with a capacity exceeding 2,000 people. Research facilities include advanced laboratories in engineering and chemistry, providing strong infrastructure for scientific work.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Dormitories</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">YTÜ offers accommodation for 2,500 students at Davutpaşa Campus and additional dormitories in cooperation with KYK. Rooms house 2-4 students and include beds, wardrobes, desks, and internet access. Dormitories feature laundry facilities, kitchens, and study rooms. Security is ensured with 24-hour camera surveillance, and regular cleaning is performed. Canteens meet basic needs. Dormitories are close to classrooms. Applications are submitted online, and incentives are provided for scholarship students. Dormitories support campus life with a comfortable environment.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Social Life</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Yıldız Technical University offers a rich social life. The historic character of Yıldız Campus and the green spaces of Davutpaşa create a peaceful environment. Sports facilities include basketball courts, tennis courts, and fitness centers, with teams achieving success in tournaments. Cafeterias provide daily meals; vegan options are limited but available upon request. There are over 100 student clubs (e.g., YTÜ Robotics Club), along with conferences, exhibitions, and festivals. The “YTÜ Spring Festival” enlivens the campus with concerts and cultural events. Istanbul’s central location enriches social life with theaters and cultural venues. Special events are organized for international students.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">International students seeking more information about university life in Turkey can visit the Road to Study platform.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Cultural Adaptation for International Students</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Yıldız Technical University hosts over 2,000 international students from more than 60 countries. The International Relations Office provides orientation programs and counseling services. Turkish language courses are offered by the Language Center at levels A1-C1 to facilitate adaptation. Through Erasmus+ and Mevlana programs, the university collaborates with more than 300 universities. Events such as “International Culture Day” promote cultural interaction. A mentorship system helps newcomers integrate into campus life. Turkey’s cultural heritage offers international students a unique experience.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Health Services and Safety</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">YTÜ provides healthcare services on campuses through the Mediko-Social Center. Weekday consultations and emergency care are available, with 24/7 ambulance service. Psychological counseling is offered through individual therapy sessions, with online appointment scheduling. Security is ensured with 24-hour camera surveillance and personnel, and entry-exit is controlled. Fire drills are conducted regularly, and buildings are equipped with safety equipment. YTÜ prioritizes student health and safety.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Transportation</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Yıldız Campus in Beşiktaş is accessible by metro (M2), bus, and ferry. Davutpaşa Campus in Esenler is reachable via metrobüs and bus lines. Free shuttle services operate between campuses according to class schedules. Bicycle paths and parking areas are available. Atatürk Airport is 20 km away and Sabiha Gökçen Airport is 45 km away, with public transportation discounts available through IstanbulKart.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Student Support Services</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">YTÜ provides internship and job opportunities through its Career Center and organizes “Career Days.” Academic advisors guide students in course selection and career planning. The Psychological Support Unit promotes mental well-being through free therapy sessions. The Disabled Student Office ensures accessibility and exam arrangements. The Scholarship Office coordinates government and foundation scholarships, and the mentorship program supports new students.</p>', '$.wp_published_at', '2025-10-07T12:41:22Z', '$.wp_modified_at', '2025-10-07T12:42:09Z') WHERE "collection" = 'pages' AND "id" = ( SELECT "live_revision_id" FROM "ec_pages" WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'yildiz-technical-university' );
